summary: One of the spoilers said that while Jonerys are having their dumb How to Train Your Dragon Moment, the three advisers see and...
question: One of the spoilers said that while Jonerys are having their dumb How to Train Your Dragon Moment, the three advisers see and start talking about how it would be a good idea for the couple to marry for 'personal' and 'political' reasons. Also, only Tyrion knows about the boatbang. But thanks for agreeing with me about why it would be political suicide for Dany to marry Jon now that he's (supposedly) been reduced to a powerless bastard Warden rather than when he was king in his own right.
answer:
I didn’t see that before @gilly-flowers @stardyng have you seen this because I will die laughing. After watching Dany and Jon get attacked, Dany’s advisors respond to a dumbass dragon ride positively? They’re not worried about how that would look? How many times did Jonerys have (bad) sex that Varys doesn’t know it’s happening?

Still Dany gains nothing from a Jon marriage especially when six other kingdoms haven’t knelt to her. Edmure would be a better option as he is related to the Starks and Robert Arryn, Blackfish worked with Yohn Royce, etc. She gets more connections with him than with Jon. Plus he already has a son and since she’s infertile, the baby can be her heir. Alo freeing the Riverlands from Lannister could give her a lot of positive PR.
